    <b class="panel-title"><u>About PRPS</u></b>
    <p class="text-justify">
        PRAN-RFL Public School (PRPS) is an educative initiative by PRAN-RFL Group with a view to providing high standard of education to the children of its   employees   and compatriots. It’s   totally a non-profit institute, established in 2014 from the point of CSR (Corporate Social Responsibilities) view.<br />
    </p>
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <div class="newsBox">
            <div class="thumbnail">
                <figure>
                    <img src="/Images/Banner/prpsleaflet.jpg" />
                </figure>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-justify">
        Major Gen Amjad Khan Chowdhury (Retd), CEO, PRAN-RFL Group and founder of this great institute dreamt to make PRPS a leading educational institute in the country by providing the community with quality, time standard education, education-friendly facilities and congenial environment required  to learn and grow to the fullest sense.<br />
        Facilities include high standard teaching staff, well-equipped and well-decorated specious classroom, computer lab, large campus and open fields for running wide range of sports and extra-curricular activities throughout the year. Alongside proper education we create fun-loving and caring atmosphere for intellectual growth of little angles and students in the upper classes.
    </p>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>Our Vision& Mission</u></b>
    <p class="text-justify">
        Education is the birthright of every child. A child is born with immense potentialities that help a nation reach new heights of success and prosperity. For fulfilling this purpose in true manner, there is no substitute to proper education in an open and learning environment.<br />
        The PRAN-RFL Public School is such a seat of education where students are the centre of every learning activity, where personal attention is given to every child to discover latent potentials. So, our mission is to nurture each and every child, focus on physical and intellectual development of students, shape and mold the children who will one day be good leaders and define who we are as a community and as a nation.<br />
        <br />
        To achieve this mission PRPS is committed to
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Going extra mile to develop little angels and young people to create a big picture , bright future and peaceful world.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Providing them with compassionate academic care to build up their career.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Ensuring a wide range of extra-curricular activities including indoor and outdoor games and sports to grow their mental and physical capacity.</li>
    </ul>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>Why PRPS</u></b>
    <p class="text-justify">
        The latent potentials of students are discovered that provide them a chance to explore their individuality and help them   build their careers<br />
        PRPS is an attractive educational institute because of the following special features-
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Well-secured campus in a convenient location</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Qualified teaching staff with different educational background and knowledge</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Students getting Much more than just a school education</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> A wide range of extra-curricular activities in a large playground and sound environment throughout the year</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Library Using facility to read books on varied topics and titles</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Well-decorated specious classrooms with modern teaching aids (large digital monitor, laptop, pictures, etc.)</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Computer Lab for ICT education</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Regular meetings and communication with guardians throughout the year to inform them of the progress of their children</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Attendance Alert System (in Process)</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Regular inspection to ensure students’ progress and uplift their understanding on academic and discipline issues</li>
    </ul>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>Teaching Staff</u></b>
    <p class="text-justify">
        Principal is Professional teacher having 10 years of experience as principal in a leading English Medium Institute. He is leading a team of qualified and experienced teachers with different educational background & knowledge.<br />
        Drawing teachers is with Fine Arts background and cultural coordinator is with special background having vast experience of national and overseas culture.<br />
        Physical instructor’s hiring is under process. Good instructor having sports background and professional experience of running sports and parade will be hired soon.

    </p>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>Teaching Methods</u></b>
    <p class="text-justify">
        The overall teaching approach of PRPS is effective, integrated and time standard. We focus on teachers’ performance and learners’ participation in classroom practice.
    </p>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>To Make It Happen PRPS Follows</u></b>
    <ul>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Active learning Methods (such as brainstorming, pair & group work etc.)</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Techniques of assessment and evaluation</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Lesson planning & use of digital content in the class</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Various games, refreshers and co-curricular activities</li>
    </ul>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>Curriculum</u></b>
    <p class="text-justify">
        Students learn best when they are active and involved, when they are encouraged to think for themselves and when they participate in solving their own problems and challenges. The curriculum therefore focuses on student-centered learning using appropriate teaching and learning strategies such as group and active learning. Basic literacy level skills are consistently emphasized in the classroom.<br />
        Interactive education encourages students to ask questions, pursue independent lines of inquiry and develop interest and expertise in a broad range of knowledge.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Beside compulsory subjects and text books, some extra books are included in the syllabus to build strong foundation of students.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Special attention is given to English to develop speaking, listening, reading and writing skill up to the mark.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Special classes are taken to improve learners’ pronunciation and fluency in English.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> In addition, much importance is given on hand writing.</li>
    </ul>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>Admission Policy</u></b>
    <ul>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> PRPS admits children of all races, colors, national and ethnic origins and ensures all right, privileges, programs, and activities generally accorded or made available to the students at the school. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, national and ethnic origin in the administration of our educational policies.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Prospective students will have to qualify in admission test to take admission in PRPS. No admission test will be held for entry class.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Children aged 4-5 years are eligible for admission in the entry class of the school.</li>
    </ul>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>School Uniform and Rules:</u></b>
    <ul>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Students must maintain dress code during academic hour.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> School remains closed on Friday as weekly holiday.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> If any student remains absent from school, his/her parents should submit an application in the school within 3 dayes.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> If any student remains absent from school for a month without informing school authority, his/her name will be struck off the roll.</li>
    </ul>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>Students Assessment</u></b>
    <ul>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Three major exams from nursery to five and 2 major exams from six to Eight are held in a year.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Before each exam adequate number of  class tests are taken.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Final Result is made on average marks of major exams.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Before each exam a number of reading, spelling and dictation tests are taken.</li>
    </ul>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>Extra-curricular Activities</u></b>
    <p class="text-justify">
        In order to make the students physically and mentally strong, we arrange games & sports and a wide range of extra-curricular activities throughout the year.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Cultural program and other programs on the occasion of various national days are organized.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Students achieving 1st, 2nd and 3rd places in the preceding year merit list are awarded.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Students standing 1st, 2nd and 3rd positions in any competition and extra-cultural activities are awarded.</li>
    </ul>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>Steps Taken to Grow Nationalism</u></b>
    <p class="text-justify">
        All the national days are observed in the school premises to awaken the nationalism in the students.
    </p>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>Fee Structure</u></b>
    <p class="text-justify">
        PRPS follows a quite reasonable fee structure which is lower than other institutions with the aim of providing service to the larger group of people in the community.<br />
        To make our dream true we mould students in such way that a student does
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Feel proud of the nation and develop self consciousness</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Build himself/herself as a responsible one</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Show due respect to teachers and parents</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Develop creativity and individually in them</li>
    </ul>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>Syllabus before Academic year</u></b>
    <p class="text-justify">
        Guardians are provided with the syllabus before an academic year starts.<br />
        To complete the syllabus is not our main goal but to get into the depth of the topic is our aim.
    </p>
    <b class="panel-title"><u>Yearly Holiday</u></b>
    <p class="text-justify">
        The holidays are determined as per the list of govt. holidays.<br />
        Other optional holidays are considered in the school holidays.<br />
        <b>PRPS dreams to make a student a complete human being and we strongly believe that this dream will become true.</b>
    </p>
